docs.abstract: Iranian hackers, computer security experts say, had been deterred by the nuclear deal, but could now be inspired to make more retaliatory assaults.
docs.snippet: Iranian hackers, computer security experts say, had been deterred by the nuclear deal, but could now be inspired to make more retaliatory assaults.
docs.lead_paragraph: Inside the Pentagon’s cyberwarfare unit, analysts have been closely monitoring internet traffic out of Iran. Six thousand miles away, Israel’s elite cyber intelligence Unit 8200 has been running war games in anticipation of Iranian strikes on Israeli computer networks.

headline.main: Without Nuclear Deal, U.S. Expects Resurgence in Iranian Cyberattacks
headline.print_headline: Without Constraints on Tehran, Experts Warn of Iranian Cyberattacks

docs.abstract: Spurred by an underserved market, entrepreneurs are offering personalized service to women seeking stylish clothing in larger sizes.
docs.snippet: Spurred by an underserved market, entrepreneurs are offering personalized service to women seeking stylish clothing in larger sizes.
docs.lead_paragraph: Nadia Boujarwah knows personally that shopping for plus-size clothes can be difficult. But it was only while she was a student at Harvard Business School that she realized something else: The lack of options presented a commercial opportunity.

headline.main: Bringing a Personal Touch to Plus-Size Fashion
headline.print_headline: Bringing a Personal Touch to Plus-Size Fashion

docs.abstract: Slashing corporate taxes last month was a Republican success. But the wrangling over a shutdown is indicative of the partisan deadlock to come.

docs.lead_paragraph: Tax cuts are looking like a rare win for President Trump. His first anniversary in the White House on Saturday coincides with a possible federal funding hiatus. headline.main: Trump’s Win on Tax Cuts Could End Up a Rare One

docs.abstract: Samantha Barry, a producer at CNN Worldwide from Cork, Ireland, is set to become the eighth editor of the women’s magazine, succeeding Cindi Leive.

docs.lead_paragraph: When Samantha Barry was growing up in Ireland, she and her family would gather around the television to watch the 6 o’clock news. They also told stories around the dinner table and read a number of newspapers and magazines, including Vogue and old issues of Time.

docs.abstract: Toby Emmerich, who helped shepherd “The Lord of the Rings” films to the screen, will oversee the studio’s worldwide film production, marketing and distribution.
docs.snippet: Toby Emmerich, who helped shepherd “The Lord of the Rings” films to the screen, will oversee the studio’s worldwide film production, marketing and distribution.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Ending a power struggle in its senior ranks, Warner Bros. on Tuesday gave control of worldwide film production, marketing and distribution to Toby Emmerich, who rose through the studio by finding hits like “It” and shepherding “The Lord of the Rings” movies.

headline.main: Warner Bros. Shakes Up Senior Film Ranks, Ending a Power Struggle
headline.print_headline: Warner Bros. Shakes Up Film Studio’s Hierarchy

docs.abstract: The Abraaj Group, a top investor in the developing world, faces questions from the World Bank and other investors.
docs.snippet: The Abraaj Group, a top investor in the developing world, faces questions from the World Bank and other investors.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Abraaj Group has  a reputation as one of the developing world’s largest and most influential investors. The private equity firm, based in Dubai, in the United Arab Emirates, manages nearly $14 billion for institutions including development agencies in the United States, Britain and France.

headline.main: Leading Private Equity Firm Accused of Misusing Funds
headline.print_headline: Investors Say A Manager  Of $14 Billion  Misused Funds

docs.abstract: The deal is the latest move by the food and beverage conglomerate to increase its offerings of healthy snacks.
docs.snippet: The deal is the latest move by the food and beverage conglomerate to increase its offerings of healthy snacks.
docs.lead_paragraph: Continuing to bet that consumers want to crunch on healthier snack items, the food and beverage giant PepsiCo announced Friday that it was acquiring Bare Foods, a maker of baked fruit and vegetable snacks.
